## How to run this series

### Option A: Run on Android Emulator

```bash
cd mobile_app

# Install Flutter dependencies
flutter pub get

# Run on connected device or emulator
flutter run
```

### Option B: Run on Chrome (for quick testing)

```bash
cd mobile_app
flutter run -d chrome
```

### Option C: Build APK

```bash
cd mobile_app
flutter build apk --release
```

### Important: Server URL configuration

| Platform | Default URL | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Android Emulator | `http://10.0.2.2:8000` | `10.0.2.2` maps to host `localhost` |
| iOS Simulator | `http://localhost:8000` | Direct localhost works |
| Physical device (WiFi) | `http://YOUR_PC_IP:8000` | Use your machine's local IP |
| Chrome | `http://localhost:8000` | Direct localhost works |

Change the server URL in the Settings screen within the app.

### Prerequisites
- Inference server running: `uvicorn inference.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000`
- Flutter SDK installed (v3.16+)
- Android Studio / Xcode for emulator

